# Merge drivers for append-only files.
# Union merge takes all lines from all branches — safe for PROSE that only ever grows
# (CHANGELOG entries, per-doc changelog footers). Prevents spurious conflicts during octopus
# and swarm merges without requiring a custom driver script.
#
# NOT union-merged (deliberately): tools/github/idmap.tsv and tools/github/issues.yaml are
# STRUCTURED, orchestrator-owned files with a hard uniqueness invariant (exactly one row/entry
# per task-id). They are never edited by parallel agents (the orchestrator owns them — CLAUDE.md
# §Swarm), so union-merge gives no benefit and actively HARMS: across a squash-divergent or
# cross-branch merge it silently appends BOTH sides, producing duplicate task-id rows / YAML keys
# that are syntactically valid but semantically broken (CLAUDE.md swarm mitigation #2). They use
# the default 3-way merge instead, so any genuine collision surfaces as an explicit conflict to
# reconcile — never a silent duplicate (G2).

CHANGELOG.md            merge=union
docs/notes/*.md          merge=union
docs/rfcs/*.md           merge=union
docs/adr/*.md            merge=union
